Boil a large #pot{} of @water{to taste}(salted) for the @potatoes{3}.

Peel the potatoes and chop into 2cm chunks.

Cook the potatoes in the boiling water until fork tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste} and a splash of @?milk{to taste} or water and mash with
a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, zest half the @lemon{1/2}(zested) (double for 4p). Cut into 4 wedges.

Season the @21 Day Aged Irish Sirloin Steak{250%g} with salt and pepper.

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets. Halve any large florets. Roughly chop the
@hazelnuts{10%g}.

Place a large #pan{} over medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the chopped
hazelnuts and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the pan and toss with the lemon zest.

> TIP: Watch the hazelnuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the pan is hot, add the broccoli and fry until starting to char,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the juice of one lemon wedge (double for 4p) and a splash of water then
immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from the
pan, set aside and cover to keep warm.

> TIP: Give the pan a wipe if you like—you'll be using it later!

Add a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and return the pan to high heat.

Once hot, fry the steak until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it more well-done.
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.
> Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, remove from pan, cover with foil and allow to rest.

Return the pan to high heat, add the @Red Wine Jus{1%sachet} and bring to the boil.

Add a splash of water to loosen if required.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice the steak.

Divide the steak between plates.

Dish up a spoonful of creamy mashed potato.

Serve the broccoli alongside with the lemony toasted hazelnuts sprinkled over.

Finish with a drizzle of the red wine jus over the steak slices.